The Kogi State Police Command on Sunday confirmed three persons dead during Saturday’s governorship election in the state. <img class=" wp-image-1289588" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Kogi-Election-1.jpg?resize=640%2C418&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="418" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Kogi-Election-1.jpg?resize=300%2C196&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Kogi-Election-1.jpg?resize=768%2C501&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Kogi-Election-1.jpg?resize=58%2C38&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Kogi-Election-1.jpg?resize=260%2C170&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Kogi-Election-1.jpg?resize=200%2C130&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Kogi-Election-1.jpg?resize=560%2C365&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Kogi-Election-1.jpg?w=878&amp;ssl=1 878w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The state Commission of Police, Mr. Akeem Busari, who confirmed the deaths to journalists, said the command was still compiling its report on the poll to ascertain the actual number of casualties. Busari also said 10 persons were arrested across the state during the election. He said three persons died in Lokoja when armed thugs invaded St. Luke Primary School, Adanakolo, during the election. Busari, however, described the situation in the state as calm. (NAN)  Vanguard The Police in Kogi has confirmed the killing of three persons during the Presidential and National Assembly elections in the state. February 24, 2019 In "News" At least 18 political parties taking part in the November 16 governorship election in Kogi have signed a Peace Accord to ensure the peaceful conduct of the poll. The accord was signed under the auspices of the National Peace Committee (NPC) at the end of a dialogue with stakeholders on… November 7, 2019 In "News" Barely five days to the governorship election in Kogi State, suspected thugs have set fire to the Secretariat of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) in Lokoja. November 11, 2019 In "News"